{"/service/ndnp/fu/batch_fu_madison_ver01/data/sn95047168/00541310514/1949040801/0113.xml":{"full_text":"Union County jlimes\nLEX GREEN, Publisher Editor-In-Chief\nAL PARKER Managing-Editor\nPublished Every Friday at Lake Butler, Florida\nEntered as second class mail matter April 8, 1921, at the Post\nOffice at Lake Butler, Florida under the Act of March 1879.\nMEMBER\nTAXING AND SPENDING\nState Senate President Brackin of Crestview is defi\nnitely correct in admonishing the legiislators to halt waste\nful spending practices before levying new taxes.\nAt the last session of the legislature a joint Senate-\nHouse tax study committee was created and appointed. This\ncommittee has just made recommendations to the pending\nsession of the Legislature for elimination of waste, foolish\nspending, and dupulication of state activities. Ihe adoption\nof this report by the Legislature would lessen the number\nof employees, of some cabinet members and bureaucrats\nand would take off the state pay roll useless and surplus,\nemployees. Of course, those affected are crying out lor\nthe Leegislature to protect them and keep them on the\nstate payroll regardless to public interest or demand.\nWe understand the existing state budget is about $156,-1\n000,000 but that the spend cravers are asking for an in-;\ncrease to bring the total spending up to about $206,000,000.1\nThis represents about 25 per cent increase in state squan-l\ndering and spending even though unemployment and eco\nnomic conditions in the state may grow worse daily for\nsome time.\nWe ask the legislators this question:\nAre you increasing overhead and expenditures and sal\naries in your own business or are you retrenching and al\nready cutting benefits and salaries of your employees?\nIn your own business or profession or trade are you\nmaking more in 1949 than you made in 1948 or 1947?\nNinety-eight per cent of individuals with whom we\nhave talked during the past few months inndicate that\ntheir own income is decreasing, whether the individual is\na business man, an employee or a professional man.\nWe cannot understand how any conscientious member\nof the Legislature can now saddle additional expenditures\nand tax burdens upon the people of the state in view of\nthe present economic and business outlook in the state. We\nbelieve the Legislature should, instead of seeking taxes to\nincrase spending and squandering by 25 per cent, look to\nwards reduction of state spending by, say, 10 per cent.\nDaily reports in the press indicate a general decline in\nemployment, mounting unemployment, salary cutting, wage\nreduction, commodity price cutting and a general road of\nbusiness decline and perhaps not only a recession but a de\npression of extensive proportions.\nIn our state and neighboring states pulp mill operations\nare being suspended or retrenched because the companies\ndo not have orders for their products. This same thing ob\ntains in other industries in our state.\nWe trust that the Legislators will follow Senate Presi\ndent Brackin in his drive for economy and elimination of\nduplication and waste in state government and will trim\nexisting state budgets instead of imposing additional taxes\nupon the backs of Florida's people for additional and un\nnecesary extravagance and spending.\nCemetery Working\nA cemetery working at Elzey\nChapel Cemetery, Friday, April)\nBth. All interested persons are;\nurged to come prepared to work.\nSigned: O. P. Hale\nHONORING BRIDE ELECT\nMrs. Eliza Hodges. Mrs. Leoni\nParrish, Mrs. E. L. Brannen and\nMrs. Virgie Adams were joint\nhostesses at a shower given at the;\nhome of the formers on Wednes-|\nday, March 30th., honoring Miss\nBernice Parrish a bride elect of'\nApril 3rd. Guests were met on\narrival by Mrs. Leon Parrish,\nthen each registered in the brides\nbook over which Mrs. Virgie\nAdams presided. Games and\ncontests suitable for the occasion\nwere enjoyed. Sandwiches, cake\nannd cold drinks were served.\nAbout 75 guests were present.\nIN APPRECIATION OF THE CONTINUED\nBUSINESS ACCORDED US OVER THE PAST THREE\nQUARTERS OF A CENTURY WE ARE RENDERING\nDURING THIS ENTIRE YEAR\nFREE SICK AND CONVALESCENT\nAm balance Service\nWITHIN THIS AREA INCLUDING UNION COUNTY\n92 700\nWILSON FUNERAL HOME\nLAKE CITY, FLORIDA\nWE RECOGNIZE ALL IN SURANCE POLICIES AND\nCOOPERATE WITH ALL COMPANIES.\nUNION COUNTY TIMES, LAKE BUTLER, FLORIDA\nSUBSCRIPTION RATE\n$2.00 per year \u2014In Advance\n$1.25 six months \u2014in advance\nAdvertising Rates Cheerfully\nfurnished at th's office\nBy The Editor-in-chief\nCEMETERY WORKING\nThere will be a cemetery work\ning at Old Bethany Cemetery, Fri\nday afternoon, April Bth, all who\nare interested please come pre\npared to work.\nI'm from Milwaukee\u2014\n%l ought to know... Aim\n\nDON AMECHE\nFamous Movie Star fc^^^J\n=Ulr \u2014l\nNOTICE OF SPECIAL\nLEISLATION\nNotice is hereby given of the\nintention of the undersigned to\napply to the Legislature of the\nState of Florida, at its regular\nsession of 1949, for the passage\nof a or special act, providing for\nthe Tax Collector of Union\nCounty to receive $250.00 per\nMonth for his services instead of\nthe present salary.\nSigned, R. T. Taylor\nLAKE THEATRE\nPHONE 46\nTWO SHOWS SUNDAY 6 AND\n8 P M. MONDAY 7:30 P. M.\nSUNDAY MONDAY\nAPRIL 10-11\nYELLOW SKY\nWITH\nGregory Peck\nNEWS CARTOON\nTUESDAY\u2014 WEDNESDAY\nAPRIL 12-13\n13 RUE MADELINE\nWITH\nJames Cagney\nTHURSDAY FRIDAY\nAPRIL 14-15\nSOFIA\nALSO\nOne Touch Venus\nCARTOON\nSATURDAY\nAPRIL 16\nBAD MAN FROM MISSOURI\nNEW SERIAL SUPERMAN\nCartoon News\nCOMING SUNDAY APRIL 17\nTHREE GODFATHERS\nGAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAh\niSllhf\n\"I'm from Milwaukee\u2014\nI ought to know...\nBRIAN DONLEVY\nFamous Movie Star\n#arz BoFta CO..WLWAur.rc.*K\nSpires Store SOAP\nLake Butler, Florida (with c upon) 43\nCAMAY 6 Regular\nFRI. and SAT. APRIL Sth 9th wh un\nTIDE, Lge. Box 2\n(with coupon)\nCOFFEE Over Sea Ilb.pkg 3,2^\nNo. 2% can, California, Packed in Heavy Syrup\nI PEACHES 25^\nF